<TITLE> Saif Power Tech to handle CCT until Nov 10 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)The cabinet committee on economic affairs has approved the recommendation of a standing committee to let Saif Power Tech to handle Chittagong Container Terminal until Nov 10, the planning minister said on Wednesday. "It is not being possible to appoint any company on a permanent basis to operate the terminal due to difficulties in legal affairs," A K Khandaker told reporters after the cabinet meeting. "The government has awarded Saif Power Tech the contract to operate the port for another month in the fourth phase," he said. Saif Power Tech was earlier given work contract to handle the CCT even after its term expired in June. Esak Brothers was supposed to run the port in line with tender but it could not after allegations of irregularities in awarding the contract to the company and former shipping adviser M A Matin surfaced. Agriculture minister Motia Chowdhury, commerce minister Faruq Khan, shipping minister Shajahan Khan and LGRD minister Syed Ashraful Islam were present, among others, in the meeting. b
